1
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,959
Why are you whistling?

2
00:02:06,599 --> 00:02:08,120
It's disturbing me while I watch the news.

3
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:09,800
Fine, I won't whistle.

4
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:14,759
*The sun is setting in the west*

5
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,099
Why did you start singing now?

6
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,780
Whistling was better than that.

7
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,240
Fine, then I'll whistle.

8
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,939
Where is my hand cream?

9
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:30,379
*Applying my beloved hand cream*

10
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,639
Old Fan.

11
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:34,439
You're acting a bit strange today.

12
00:02:35,039 --> 00:02:36,319
Why are you so excited?

13
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,240
Did you find a wallet or something?

14
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:40,520
If you found a wallet, you must give it to Mr. Policeman.

15
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:43,039
Otherwise, our "Drop the Hanky" song...

16
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:44,039
...would have been sung for nothing.

17
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:47,000
Why would I sing "Drop the Hanky" if I found a wallet?

18
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:49,319
Who found a wallet?

19
00:02:49,319 --> 00:02:50,780
Then why are you so excited today?

20
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,240
Am I excited?

21
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:55,280
Today in the activity room...

22
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,800
...they're showing the old movie *Railway Guerrillas*.

23
00:02:58,159 --> 00:03:00,599
You're putting on hand cream just to watch *Railway Guerrillas*?

24
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,159
If we were watching *Taking Tiger Mountain by Strategy*...

25
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:05,520
...you'd probably be applying wax to prevent frostbite!

26
00:03:05,699 --> 00:03:07,639
Ms. Liu asked me out for tonight.

27
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:10,719
To watch the movie together.

28
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:17,199
*The sun is setting in the west*

29
00:03:17,479 --> 00:03:21,080
*The end of the devils is drawing near*

30
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,319
Why are you shaking your head at me when you mention "devils"?

31
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,000
Ms. Liu is here.

32
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,039
Liu...

33
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:30,840
...Xiao Cai.

34
00:03:31,199 --> 00:03:33,080
What kind of name is "Liu Xiao Cai"?

35
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:33,879
I'm looking for Boss Li.

36
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:34,800
Alright, you two chat.

37
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:38,020
*Strumming my beloved pipa*

38
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,000
*Singing those moving ballads*

39
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:42,439
Boss Li.

40
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,159
Keeping up with national affairs?

41
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,379
I'm just getting a grasp...

42
00:03:48,740 --> 00:03:50,879
...on the progress of the Qiongzhou Strait Bridge.

43
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,379
What do you want with me?

44
00:03:55,439 --> 00:03:56,800
You probably don't know yet, right?

45
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:59,719
Our community is hosting an old movie retrospective.

46
00:03:59,879 --> 00:04:01,280
Tonight they're showing that...

47
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,000
...that...

48
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:04,120
...what's it called again?

49
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,240
*Railway Guerrillas*.

50
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:08,080
My goodness, you've grasped that too?

51
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:08,879
Heh.

52
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:10,159
That's impressive.

53
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,159
Guess what?

54
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,840
I've been watching this movie since I was a kid.

55
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,360
But I never really understood it.

56
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:16,079
Today is a good chance.

57
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,000
Ms. Liu...

58
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,759
...went to watch it with Old Fan.

59
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,040
My goodness, you've grasped that situation too?

60
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,279
That's so impressive.

61
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,519
So...

62
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,959
I was thinking...

63
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,240
...that you and I...

64
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,040
You and me?

65
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,120
What would people say if they saw that?

66
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:31,920
I'm not going.

67
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:33,839
Hey...

68
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:36,439
Why is being with me "improper"?

69
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:38,100
Suit yourself.

70
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,220
If you won't go, forget it!

71
00:04:39,319 --> 00:04:40,199
Honestly.

72
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:46,079
*The sun is setting in the west*

73
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:04,240
*The sun is setting in the west*

74
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:28,379
Order something expensive, everyone.

75
00:05:28,379 --> 00:05:30,019
Don't try to save me money.

76
00:05:30,019 --> 00:05:31,259
Then I won't hold back.

77
00:05:32,139 --> 00:05:34,139
Let's have braised prawns.

78
00:05:34,139 --> 00:05:34,860
Alright.

79
00:05:35,259 --> 00:05:36,060
Old Fan.

80
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:37,339
Don't be stingy.

81
00:05:37,339 --> 00:05:38,699
I can pay for this myself.

82
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:40,259
What kind of talk is that?

83
00:05:40,259 --> 00:05:41,660
Why would I be stingy?

84
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:43,939
Since that's the case.

85
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:46,620
Then let's have the one-pound braised prawns.

86
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:47,740
One for each person.

87
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:49,019
Do you have...

88
00:05:50,699 --> 00:05:52,660
...one-pound prawns?

89
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:53,500
Why wouldn't there be?

90
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,300
This big.

91
00:05:56,019 --> 00:05:57,379
Red ones, I've seen them.

92
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:58,899
Just the claws weigh half a pound.

93
00:05:58,899 --> 00:06:00,339
You're talking about lobster.

94
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,459
You said it.

95
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:03,459
Serve lobster.

96
00:06:03,639 --> 00:06:04,399
Boss Li.

97
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,300
We aren't a seafood restaurant.

98
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,620
We don't have lobster.

99
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,379
You don't?

100
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,259
Then he got off cheap.

101
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,220
Wang Song.

102
00:06:11,779 --> 00:06:12,980
As long as there's lobster here.

103
00:06:13,139 --> 00:06:14,300
Keep them coming.

104
00:06:14,699 --> 00:06:16,019
Don't try to save me money.

105
00:06:16,339 --> 00:06:17,139
Do you have it?

106
00:06:17,379 --> 00:06:18,139
No.

107
00:06:18,139 --> 00:06:19,339
That, we can have.

108
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:20,379
That...

109
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,420
We really don't.

110
00:06:22,459 --> 00:06:23,259
Old Fan.

111
00:06:24,379 --> 00:06:26,100
Why so generous today?

112
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,420
Treating everyone to a meal?

113
00:06:31,139 --> 00:06:32,139
I get it.

114
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,860
The wallet you found last night...

115
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,379
...you didn't give to Mr. Policeman.

116
00:06:36,379 --> 00:06:37,620
Who didn't give it to the police?

117
00:06:38,319 --> 00:06:40,019
Who found a wallet?

118
00:06:40,019 --> 00:06:41,660
Then where did you get the money to treat us?

119
00:06:41,819 --> 00:06:42,779
And ordering lobster too.

120
00:06:42,779 --> 00:06:43,980
Who ordered lobster?

121
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,579
This place definitely doesn't have lobster, right?

122
00:06:47,819 --> 00:06:49,379
Since you won't tell the truth.

123
00:06:49,379 --> 00:06:50,980
We shouldn't ask too much.

124
00:06:51,379 --> 00:06:53,120
But using money from unknown sources...

125
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,180
...to treat us to dinner...

126
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:55,660
...we won't eat this meal.

127
00:06:55,899 --> 00:06:56,899
Right, everyone?

128
00:06:56,899 --> 00:06:57,699
Let's go.

129
00:06:57,699 --> 00:06:58,420
Let's leave.

130
00:06:58,420 --> 00:06:59,600
Leave? Why?

131
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:00,579
Xiao Cai.

132
00:07:00,579 --> 00:07:01,100
You sit.

133
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:01,819
Going where?

134
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:02,699
Nowhere, I'm not going anywhere.

135
00:07:02,699 --> 00:07:03,720
Why are we leaving?

136
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,420
Sit down.

137
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,180
Not leaving.

138
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:06,899
Who said my money is from an unknown source?

139
00:07:06,899 --> 00:07:07,740
Then why are you hemming and hawing?

140
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:08,899
Why don't you dare say it straight?

141
00:07:08,899 --> 00:07:10,220
Who doesn't dare?

142
00:07:11,660 --> 00:07:13,259
This is money I made investing in stocks.

143
00:07:13,259 --> 00:07:14,300
Fair and square.

144
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,420
I have a student.

145
00:07:17,899 --> 00:07:20,060
From our Guanghua School of Management.

146
00:07:20,339 --> 00:07:21,779
He often advises me.

147
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:24,300
Saying money just sitting there is wasted.

148
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,459
Better to take it out.

149
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:26,860
Invest in the stock market.

150
00:07:27,139 --> 00:07:28,459
Firstly, to support national construction.

151
00:07:28,459 --> 00:07:29,980
Secondly, to make some money.

152
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:31,019
Really?

153
00:07:31,019 --> 00:07:32,379
You make it sound so real.

154
00:07:32,379 --> 00:07:33,819
Who among us believes that?

155
00:07:33,819 --> 00:07:35,180
Believe it or not.

156
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,720
Can you stop speaking for everyone?

157
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,180
Wang Song, serve the dishes.

158
00:07:39,379 --> 00:07:40,860
Wait, serve what dishes?

159
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:42,620
We haven't ordered a single hot dish yet.

160
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:43,420
Right.

161
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:45,060
Come on, let's order one to eat.

162
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:46,180
Don't fall asleep.

163
00:07:46,259 --> 00:07:46,899
Time to eat.

164
00:07:49,819 --> 00:07:50,480
Here.

165
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:52,540
Everyone, taste my tea.

166
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:53,699
It's authentic.

167
00:07:53,699 --> 00:07:54,660
Pre-Rain Maojian.

168
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:56,180
Fresh tea just harvested this year.

169
00:07:57,339 --> 00:07:57,800
Uh,

170
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,620
Old Li doesn't like tea.

171
00:07:58,620 --> 00:07:59,620
No need to pour any for him.

172
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:00,660
Why shouldn't I?

173
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:02,660
Old Fan,

174
00:08:03,459 --> 00:08:04,339
treating everyone to tea,

175
00:08:04,339 --> 00:08:06,220
can't you use a bigger teapot?

176
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,220
How is this enough for everyone?

177
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:09,579
What do you know?

178
00:08:09,579 --> 00:08:11,379
That's how Gongfu tea is supposed to be drunk.

179
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:13,579
And to think you were a boss for so many years.

180
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:14,939
What about being a boss?

181
00:08:15,379 --> 00:08:17,060
Who says it has to be drunk this way?

182
00:08:17,139 --> 00:08:18,699
Is there an official document for tea?

183
00:08:19,019 --> 00:08:20,699
Which department of the Tea Association stamped it?

184
00:08:21,899 --> 00:08:23,420
Grandpa Fan, Grandpa Li,

185
00:08:23,459 --> 00:08:25,459
why do you bicker about everything?

186
00:08:25,459 --> 00:08:26,379
Hurry up and taste it.

187
00:08:26,379 --> 00:08:27,420
It tastes really good.

188
00:08:27,699 --> 00:08:29,060
There's no hard rule,

189
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,300
but surely you've seen *Dream of the Red Chamber*?

190
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:32,620
The TV series, right?

191
00:08:33,019 --> 00:08:34,100
Which version? Which version?

192
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:34,899
I've seen them all.

193
00:08:34,899 --> 00:08:36,299
Miaoyu put it well:

194
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:38,379
One cup is for tasting,

195
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,500
two cups are for quenching thirst,

196
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,899
and someone like you,

197
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,500
holding an

198
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,779
extra-large thermos all day long,

199
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:46,299
is drinking like a mule.

200
00:08:46,779 --> 00:08:47,620
Don't get mad at me.

201
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:48,899
That's what it says in *Dream of the Red Chamber*.

202
00:08:48,899 --> 00:08:50,379
Who else should I get mad at?

203
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:52,580
Which version of *Dream of the Red Chamber* mentions a thermos?

204
00:08:52,580 --> 00:08:53,220
Find it for me.

205
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,399
Find it.

206
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:56,820
No, uh, Grandpa Fan,

207
00:08:56,820 --> 00:08:57,299
um,

208
00:08:57,299 --> 00:08:59,460
this gentleman says he has an appointment with you.

209
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:00,259
Xiao Qian!

210
00:09:00,259 --> 00:09:00,940
Hello, Professor Fan.

211
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:01,779
Come, come over here.

212
00:09:01,779 --> 00:09:03,220
Taste my Pre-Rain Maojian.

213
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,139
No thanks.

214
00:09:04,539 --> 00:09:05,340
Professor Fan,

215
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,460
let's...

216
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:07,779
speak in private.

217
00:09:10,419 --> 00:09:11,980
Making a little money from stocks,

218
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,860
what's there to hide?

219
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,419
There are no outsiders here.

220
00:09:16,419 --> 00:09:17,700
They are all my good friends.

221
00:09:18,179 --> 00:09:18,980
Everyone,

222
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:20,460
this is my student,

223
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,139
a top graduate from the School of Management,

224
00:09:22,139 --> 00:09:23,379
Qian Buyi.

225
00:09:24,059 --> 00:09:25,299
That's a good name.

226
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,299
Making money isn't easy for anyone.

227
00:09:27,779 --> 00:09:28,580
Alright then.

228
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:30,740
This here,

229
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:33,379
is the 30,000 yuan earned from this trade.

230
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,740
And the trade records,

231
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:36,139
and tax clearance certificates.

232
00:09:36,419 --> 00:09:37,500
Please count it.

233
00:09:38,059 --> 00:09:39,340
No need, Xiao Qian.

234
00:09:40,139 --> 00:09:40,940
I mean,

235
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,100
thank you for your hard work.

236
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:42,820
Xiao Qian.

237
00:09:43,179 --> 00:09:44,500
Professor, you're too kind.

238
00:09:44,580 --> 00:09:45,740
Without your mentorship,

239
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:47,299
I wouldn't be where I am today.

240
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:49,220
Professor, you guys chat.

241
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:50,100
I'll be going now.

242
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:51,659
Won't you stay a bit longer?

243
00:09:51,659 --> 00:09:52,320
No.

244
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:54,940
My car is at the gate, temporarily parked.

245
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:56,659
You drove here?

246
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:58,899
Is it that new car you got last month?

247
00:09:59,179 --> 00:10:00,259
You bought another one?

248
00:10:00,899 --> 00:10:02,460
Okay, drive safely.

249
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:03,220
Will do.

250
00:10:06,059 --> 00:10:07,120
Sit down.

251
00:10:08,019 --> 00:10:09,259
What's the big deal?

252
00:10:09,259 --> 00:10:10,379
This little bit of money.

253
00:10:10,779 --> 00:10:11,940
Back in my day,

254
00:10:12,539 --> 00:10:14,419
I'd handle millions or tens of millions a day.

255
00:10:14,419 --> 00:10:15,580
Passing through my hands.

256
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:17,700
So how much did you skim off?

257
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,340
Me?

258
00:10:18,340 --> 00:10:19,100
No.

259
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,460
Money passed through my hands,

260
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:22,740
but the motherland stayed in my heart.

261
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:24,419
Managing money and goods for thirty years,

262
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,899
with completely clean hands.

263
00:10:26,779 --> 00:10:28,019
Since you're retired now,

264
00:10:28,019 --> 00:10:29,340
you could dabble in stocks.

265
00:10:30,059 --> 00:10:31,059
Make a little money.

266
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,220
Become the first to get rich...

267
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,379
...or the ones who get rich later.

268
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,740
Look at your mindset.

269
00:10:35,539 --> 00:10:38,179
Your goal in stocks is just to rake in cash.

270
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:39,179
Getting something for nothing.

271
00:10:40,059 --> 00:10:41,860
So I've become an unscrupulous merchant?

272
00:10:42,299 --> 00:10:43,500
I wouldn't say unscrupulous merchant.

273
00:10:44,179 --> 00:10:46,100
But different from the broad masses.

274
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:47,899
Look at Master Gou.

275
00:10:48,179 --> 00:10:49,299
Relies on hard work in the fields.

276
00:10:49,659 --> 00:10:50,460
Ms. Liu,

277
00:10:50,659 --> 00:10:51,659
relies on performing for a living.

278
00:10:51,899 --> 00:10:53,539
Xiao Cai relies on matchmaking.

279
00:10:53,860 --> 00:10:55,539
Old Liang relies on his daughter's contributions.

280
00:10:55,539 --> 00:10:56,220
Wait.

281
00:10:56,539 --> 00:10:58,500
Why do you keep nagging about me?

282
00:10:59,539 --> 00:11:01,299
Fine, I can't out-talk you.

283
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:02,580
I'm going back to my room.

284
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,220
Going back won't help me avoid you.

285
00:11:05,379 --> 00:11:07,620
I'm going to Ms. Liu's room for tea.

286
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:08,899
Sister Liu,

287
00:11:09,659 --> 00:11:11,220
you wouldn't mind, would you?

288
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,139
No.

289
00:11:12,139 --> 00:11:13,759
How could I? Welcome.

290
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:14,340
Good.

291
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:16,620
Professor Fan!

292
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:18,659
Why did you leave while we were chatting?

293
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:20,139
Professor Fan!

294
00:11:20,899 --> 00:11:21,840
Don't... Xiao Cai.

295
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:22,860
Don't chase him.

296
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:23,659
Let them go.

297
00:11:25,539 --> 00:11:27,139
I have to keep an eye on things for you.

298
00:11:27,139 --> 00:11:28,340
I'll report back to you later.

299
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:28,980
This...

300
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,299
Do I need a lookout?

301
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,019
You'd better hurry up!

302
00:11:41,559 --> 00:11:42,720
Come on.

303
00:11:42,779 --> 00:11:43,500
Take the seat of honor.

304
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:43,980
Saved it for you.

305
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:44,620
Hurry, hurry.

306
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:45,279
Hurry and sit here.

307
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:45,840
I'll order.

308
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,539
I'm ordering.

309
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,179
Green pepper shredded potatoes.

310
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:51,340
Spicy shredded potato salad.

311
00:11:51,899 --> 00:11:53,460
Mustard greens and cucumber strips.

312
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:55,240
Any meat dishes? Yes.

313
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:57,299
Fish-flavored shredded pork.

314
00:11:57,980 --> 00:12:00,299
Xiaoxin, cancel all these dishes.

315
00:12:00,299 --> 00:12:01,659
Just brew us a pot of jasmine tea.

316
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:02,700
We have things to discuss.

317
00:12:02,899 --> 00:12:03,700
Okay.

318
00:12:05,179 --> 00:12:05,820
That works too.

319
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:07,620
Xiao Cai.

320
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,820
Don't beat around the bush or hide things from me.

321
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:10,779
Speak your mind.

322
00:12:10,899 --> 00:12:11,860
What do you want with me?

323
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:14,759
Here, give it to me.

324
00:12:14,759 --> 00:12:15,240
Give it to me.

325
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:16,799
Um...

326
00:12:21,399 --> 00:12:23,080
Then I'll just be straight with you, okay?

327
00:12:24,159 --> 00:12:24,960
Look...

328
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:26,440
Have a drink.

329
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,799
Today...

330
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:29,360
That student of yours came by.

331
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,879
And gave you money.

332
00:12:31,519 --> 00:12:32,820
That money...

333
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,200
It's all real, right?

334
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,200
What are you saying?

335
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,480
My student...

336
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,980
Would give me fake bills? Spirit money?

337
00:12:39,980 --> 00:12:40,600
No...

338
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,720
That's not what I meant.

339
00:12:42,399 --> 00:12:43,200
It's just...

340
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:45,919
That money is clean, right?

341
00:12:48,039 --> 00:12:49,120
That's even more outrageous.

342
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:49,879
If it's not clean...

343
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:51,000
Or was it stolen?

344
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,480
No, that's not what I meant.

345
00:12:53,279 --> 00:12:54,399
What I mean is...

346
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,399
That money really came from your stock trading, right?

347
00:12:58,399 --> 00:12:59,879
How could that be fake?

348
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:01,440
This student of mine...

349
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,679
Studied finance.

350
00:13:02,679 --> 00:13:04,399
Specializes in stock research.

351
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,639
Why?

352
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,159
Did Old Li send you to check my accounts?

353
00:13:09,399 --> 00:13:10,440
No way.

354
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,200
No one is checking up on you.

355
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,120
No.

356
00:13:13,559 --> 00:13:15,440
What I actually wanted to say is...

357
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,220
You see, I...

358
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:23,639
am not exactly well-off.

359
00:13:23,919 --> 00:13:25,299
My husband passed away early,

360
00:13:26,279 --> 00:13:27,759
living expenses are high,

361
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:30,399
my daughter-in-law is wicked,

362
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,000
and my son isn't filial.

363
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,799
Only my little grandson is sweet,

364
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,399
but he's still too young.

365
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:37,759
You tell me,

366
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,100
when this child grows up,

367
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,679
going to school, going to work,

368
00:13:40,679 --> 00:13:42,580
dating, getting married, buying a house,

369
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:44,559
doesn't everything cost money?

370
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:45,059
Right?

371
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,120
So regarding this,

372
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,519
if you don't help me,

373
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:50,600
no one else can.

374
00:13:51,879 --> 00:13:52,679
Well...

375
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:54,879
I am a...

376
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,240
single man.

377
00:13:57,799 --> 00:13:59,799
It's not quite appropriate for me to help you, is it?

378
00:13:59,919 --> 00:14:01,639
No, what are you thinking?

379
00:14:01,759 --> 00:14:02,720
You really have an imagination.

380
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:03,519
No,

381
00:14:04,559 --> 00:14:06,039
I'll be straight with you.

382
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:07,919
Can you...

383
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,840
take me along to make money in stocks?

384
00:14:11,679 --> 00:14:13,240
You want to trade stocks?

385
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,000
Yes!

386
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:15,639
You trade stocks too?

387
00:14:15,639 --> 00:14:16,799
Don't shout!

388
00:14:16,799 --> 00:14:17,440
Shh!

389
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:19,639
Don't let anyone hear.

390
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:21,080
You trade stocks too?

391
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:22,960
Of course.

392
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,480
Who doesn't want to make money?

393
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:26,120
Didn't you have a saying?

394
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,360
Money just sits there if you leave it,

395
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:30,039
but if you use it to earn,

396
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,919
one begets two, two begets three,

397
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:33,240
and three begets a million.

398
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,279
That's not certain.

399
00:14:35,399 --> 00:14:36,720
In stock trading,

400
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:38,399
you win some, you lose some.

401
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,320
What if you lose?

402
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,440
That's impossible.

403
00:14:40,759 --> 00:14:42,200
Really, who are you?

404
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,039
A great professor.

405
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,600
And who is your student?

406
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,879
Someone in finance and stocks, right?

407
00:14:46,879 --> 00:14:48,639
With such high IQs between the two of you,

408
00:14:48,639 --> 00:14:49,200
if you lose money,

409
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,919
no one can make money. No one.

410
00:14:50,919 --> 00:14:52,120
That is true,

411
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:54,279
I knew it.

412
00:14:55,799 --> 00:14:58,200
You're a brazier in June,

413
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,080
clearly a warm-hearted person.

414
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:03,200
Do you have the heart to watch someone in need like me,

415
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,960
and not lend a hand?

416
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,519
If you weren't a good person,

417
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:11,120
would Ms. Liu praise you like that behind your back?

418
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:11,960
Really?

419
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,799
Then how did Ms. Liu praise me?

420
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,320
She praised... just praised...

421
00:15:17,279 --> 00:15:18,679
Oh, how she praised you!

422
00:15:18,679 --> 00:15:19,440
What?

423
00:15:19,799 --> 00:15:20,600
Praised...

424
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:21,519
There were too many good words,

425
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:22,480
I can't even repeat them all.

426
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,360
Anyway, in a nutshell,

427
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,360
if you have trouble, find the Professor.

428
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:31,440
You should call the police if you're in trouble.

429
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,720
You handle what the police can't.

430
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,360
Can the police handle stock trading?

431
00:15:38,919 --> 00:15:39,720
Fine.

432
00:15:39,919 --> 00:15:41,679
Since you put it that way...

433
00:15:41,679 --> 00:15:42,879
I'll reluctantly...

434
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,259
...help you trade a bit.

435
00:15:45,519 --> 00:15:46,519
But let me be clear.

436
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:48,200
I'm not responsible for losses or gains.

437
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:51,320
If you're not responsible, who is?

438
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:52,559
Come on.

439
00:15:53,679 --> 00:15:55,320
That's impossible, right?

440
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,360
As long as you're involved...

441
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,960
...there's no way we'll lose.

442
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,440
It's settled then, no changes.

443
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:00,179
Honestly.

444
00:16:00,679 --> 00:16:01,720
Let me tell you...

445
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:04,039
...you have to keep this a secret for me.

446
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,200
Don't tell anyone else.

447
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,240
Okay, I will.

448
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,299
You know why I won't tell anyone?

449
00:16:10,059 --> 00:16:12,299
I can't let my daughter-in-law know about this.

450
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:14,460
The money I'm using for stocks...

451
00:16:14,460 --> 00:16:16,620
...is my secret stash and nest egg.

452
00:16:17,659 --> 00:16:19,019
If that little vixen finds out...

453
00:16:19,019 --> 00:16:21,220
...who knows what stunt she'll pull.

454
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:23,720
Okay, I'll keep it a secret.

455
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:24,980
So, how much do you plan...

456
00:16:25,019 --> 00:16:26,100
...to put in?

457
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:27,019
To buy stocks.

458
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:31,299
If we're buying, let's go big.

459
00:16:31,299 --> 00:16:33,059
I'll put in 200 yuan.

460
00:16:35,539 --> 00:16:36,340
Two hundred?

461
00:16:37,299 --> 00:16:37,799
You should keep that...

462
00:16:37,799 --> 00:16:39,379
...to buy lollipops for your grandson.

463
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:41,580
Too little? I can add more.

464
00:16:41,779 --> 00:16:43,059
How about 230?

465
00:16:43,059 --> 00:16:43,779
Two hundred...

466
00:16:44,279 --> 00:16:45,379
Professor...

467
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:46,419
Two hundred and fifty.

468
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:47,740
Is 250 okay?

469
00:16:58,899 --> 00:16:59,700
Come in.

470
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:02,500
Professor Fan.

471
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:04,099
Boss Li isn't here, is he?

472
00:17:04,579 --> 00:17:05,900
He went to do Tai Chi.

473
00:17:06,339 --> 00:17:08,140
Why are you being so sneaky?

474
00:17:08,619 --> 00:17:09,859
Good, he's not here.

475
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:13,740
Professor Fan.

476
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:16,240
I just withdrew this from the bank.

477
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,920
Ten thousand yuan.

478
00:17:18,539 --> 00:17:19,900
Count it.

479
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,539
It is ten thousand.

480
00:17:23,019 --> 00:17:24,059
This is just pocket change.

481
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:26,019
I mean, this is what you call pocket change.

482
00:17:26,019 --> 00:17:26,859
Qian Buyi.

483
00:17:27,059 --> 00:17:29,140
Invest this money in the stock market ASAP.

484
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:30,059
Buy stocks with it.

485
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:35,019
Professor Fan, this is my nest egg.

486
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,859
Shouldn't we find a stock...

487
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:40,819
...that only makes a profit?

488
00:17:41,579 --> 00:17:43,059
Is there such a stock?

489
00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:45,420
Didn't I tell you already?

490
00:17:45,819 --> 00:17:46,859
No one can guarantee...

491
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:48,019
...a profit without loss.

492
00:17:51,099 --> 00:17:52,259
If that's your requirement...

493
00:17:52,259 --> 00:17:53,059
Sister Cai...

494
00:17:53,099 --> 00:17:55,180
...I suggest you don't trade.

495
00:17:55,420 --> 00:17:56,140
No...

496
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:56,640
No...

497
00:17:57,059 --> 00:17:57,980
I was just joking with you.

498
00:17:57,980 --> 00:17:59,180
Don't take it seriously.

499
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,599
No, it's just...

500
00:18:00,599 --> 00:18:02,299
If I happen to lose it...

501
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:06,099
I'll just treat it as a contribution to national construction.

502
00:18:07,220 --> 00:18:07,900
That's not it...

503
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:10,140
The country isn't short of my money, right?

504
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:10,859
You say...

505
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:11,579
Just rest assured.

506
00:18:11,579 --> 00:18:12,859
Leave it to me, okay?

507
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:20,299
You're such a big professor,

508
00:18:21,059 --> 00:18:22,500
folding your own bedding?

509
00:18:22,599 --> 00:18:23,859
Let me do it.

510
00:18:23,859 --> 00:18:24,660
This is my bedding.

511
00:18:24,660 --> 00:18:25,960
Why should I trouble you to fold it?

512
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:26,380
Don't.

513
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,500
I should. You even helped me make money.

514
00:18:29,059 --> 00:18:31,539
I can't guarantee I'll make you money.

515
00:18:31,539 --> 00:18:32,900
Then I must help even more.

516
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:33,579
I'll do it.

517
00:18:33,799 --> 00:18:34,740
Let me do it.

518
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,299
You...

519
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:37,859
What's going on here?

520
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:40,339
Playing tug-of-war?

521
00:18:40,380 --> 00:18:41,180
No.

522
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:41,819
No.

523
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,980
I was actually...

524
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:45,660
trying to tidy up this bed for you.

525
00:18:45,660 --> 00:18:47,740
Look, it's so neat.

526
00:18:47,740 --> 00:18:48,539
I took one look,

527
00:18:48,539 --> 00:18:50,019
and I just helped Professor Fan

528
00:18:50,019 --> 00:18:51,299
fold it a little.

529
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:53,660
Is today International Bed-Folding Day?

530
00:18:53,859 --> 00:18:55,420
No.

531
00:18:55,660 --> 00:18:57,180
Everyone has two hands.

532
00:18:57,660 --> 00:18:58,460
Old Fan,

533
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:00,259
can't you fold your own quilt?

534
00:19:01,299 --> 00:19:02,819
Don't expect to be waited on hand and foot.

535
00:19:02,819 --> 00:19:03,420
That's not it.

536
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:04,980
Maids make beds, laborers walk dogs.

537
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:05,500
No...

538
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:05,920
It's...

539
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:06,859
Lazy and stupid.

540
00:19:06,859 --> 00:19:07,660
Decadent and rotten.

541
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:08,380
No, I...

542
00:19:08,819 --> 00:19:09,619
Xiao Cai,

543
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:11,539
if Old Fan bullies you again in the future,

544
00:19:11,539 --> 00:19:12,240
just tell me.

545
00:19:12,859 --> 00:19:13,819
I'll deal with him.

546
00:19:15,059 --> 00:19:16,579
I'm so wronged.

547
00:19:22,019 --> 00:19:24,299
Lower. Right level carry.

548
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:27,940
Left level carry. Retract foot.

549
00:19:28,339 --> 00:19:30,220
Twist waist, swing sword.

550
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:32,140
One-legged swing and chop.

551
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:37,400
Professor Fan, you scared me to death!

552
00:19:37,579 --> 00:19:38,180
Are you okay?

553
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,140
This one-legged swing and chop...

554
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:40,500
is really hard to balance.

555
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:41,079
Right.

556
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:41,920
Professor Fan,

557
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:44,000
you don't get enough exercise.

558
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,319
Ms. Liu,

559
00:19:45,319 --> 00:19:46,759
look at you, going left and right,

560
00:19:46,759 --> 00:19:47,960
swinging wildly,

561
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:48,759
and chopping away.

562
00:19:48,759 --> 00:19:49,799
Look at Professor Fan,

563
00:19:49,799 --> 00:19:50,880
his forehead is covered in sweat.

564
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,759
Why don't we let him rest a bit?

565
00:19:52,759 --> 00:19:53,819
No, I'm not tired.

566
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:54,500
I'm not tired.

567
00:19:54,779 --> 00:19:55,559
Xiao Cai,

568
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:56,680
why don't you find somewhere cool

569
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,799
and go rest there for a while?

570
00:19:57,799 --> 00:19:58,559
What are you saying?

571
00:19:58,559 --> 00:20:00,119
You've practiced so long and aren't tired?

572
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,759
I'm tired just watching from the side.

573
00:20:01,759 --> 00:20:02,880
That's ridiculous.

574
00:20:03,519 --> 00:20:05,759
Ms. Liu is tired.

575
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,079
How about, Ms. Liu,

576
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,319
you find a cool place

577
00:20:08,319 --> 00:20:09,259
to cool off?

578
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,279
Well, how about we stop here for today?

579
00:20:11,279 --> 00:20:12,000
Alright.

580
00:20:12,359 --> 00:20:14,160
I'll head back first, Professor Fan.

581
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:14,920
Don't.

582
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,559
Ms. Liu,

583
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,640
I finally managed to stand

584
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,160
with a tiny bit of improvement.

585
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,200
How can you, the master, leave now?

586
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,079
Let's keep practicing.

587
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:22,700
I'm not tired at all, really.

588
00:20:23,039 --> 00:20:25,400
You're not tired, but I am!

589
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,039
You...

590
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:28,299
Alright then, let's sit here and rest a bit.

591
00:20:28,299 --> 00:20:29,099
Then, rest here a bit.

592
00:20:29,099 --> 00:20:29,640
Okay.

593
00:20:29,859 --> 00:20:30,440
Okay.

594
00:20:30,759 --> 00:20:32,039
Alright, hold this.

595
00:20:32,039 --> 00:20:33,000
Thanks, Yingzi.

596
00:20:34,799 --> 00:20:36,240
By the way, Professor Fan,

597
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:39,359
I think besides paying attention to exercise,

598
00:20:39,359 --> 00:20:40,920
aside from that kind of activity,

599
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:41,920
it's very important

600
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,000
for us seniors

601
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,240
to watch our diet.

602
00:20:44,559 --> 00:20:45,880
We really must be careful. Right.

603
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,799
Like things high in cholesterol,

604
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,240
greasy fried foods,

605
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:50,880
and things with too much sugar or salt.

606
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:52,279
We should try to eat less of those.

607
00:20:52,799 --> 00:20:53,799
You're right.

608
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:54,799
Ms. Liu,

609
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,480
why don't you help me make a meal plan?

610
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,240
Every day, I'll follow the plan you make

611
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,000
for my meals.

612
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:00,759
Okay?

613
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:01,799
Listen to me.

614
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:04,200
Yingzi here is speaking very professionally.

615
00:21:05,559 --> 00:21:06,200
All right then.

616
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:06,740
Then I...

617
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:07,039
Here...

618
00:21:07,039 --> 00:21:08,519
I'll give you a little advice.

619
00:21:09,079 --> 00:21:09,759
For breakfast,

620
00:21:09,759 --> 00:21:10,519
for example,

621
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,279
drink milk and eat eggs.

622
00:21:13,519 --> 00:21:15,640
You should avoid fried dough sticks.

623
00:21:16,839 --> 00:21:18,200
Good thing you said that.

624
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,440
I just love fried dough sticks.

625
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,200
You kid, just eat as much as you like.

626
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,200
What business is it of yours?

627
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:23,680
Professor Fan,

628
00:21:23,779 --> 00:21:24,200
we, uh...

629
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,160
I think what Ms. Liu said

630
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,400
really makes sense.

631
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,759
Starting tomorrow,

632
00:21:27,759 --> 00:21:28,480
fried dough sticks...

633
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:29,599
I'm quitting them.

634
00:21:29,819 --> 00:21:30,799
Quitting.

635
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:31,559
Well, no...

636
00:21:31,559 --> 00:21:32,880
Listen to me, listen.

637
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,039
It's not that absolute.

638
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,119
Usually,

639
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:39,160
eating just a little bit is still okay.

640
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,839
Right, eat less.

641
00:21:41,599 --> 00:21:42,400
Ms. Liu,

642
00:21:43,039 --> 00:21:44,539
Yusheng is looking for you.

643
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,960
I forgot to tell you.

644
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,940
Look, give me that first...

645
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:48,319
Okay.

646
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:49,279
You guys keep chatting.

647
00:21:49,279 --> 00:21:50,200
I'm going to find Yusheng.

648
00:21:51,079 --> 00:21:51,700
See you later.

649
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,980
Ms. Liu, let me go with you.

650
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:55,500
Why go with her?

651
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,920
I had a hard time sending Ms. Liu away.

652
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,000
Sending her away?

653
00:21:59,599 --> 00:22:00,420
What do you mean?

654
00:22:00,799 --> 00:22:02,359
So Yusheng wasn't looking for her?

655
00:22:02,519 --> 00:22:03,720
He was looking for her,

656
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,359
but that was yesterday.

657
00:22:06,839 --> 00:22:08,640
Aren't you holding things up?

658
00:22:09,079 --> 00:22:10,279
You two are endless.

659
00:22:10,279 --> 00:22:11,759
You're holding up my business.

660
00:22:12,319 --> 00:22:13,599
What business is it?

661
00:22:13,599 --> 00:22:15,160
The stocks!

662
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,640
At eight o'clock this morning,

663
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,880
I gave you ten thousand yuan, right?

664
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,440
Right.

665
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,000
It's been six hours.

666
00:22:24,359 --> 00:22:25,759
How is my money doing?

667
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,200
You have to give me some news.

668
00:22:28,519 --> 00:22:30,720
I'm really amazed by you, sister.

669
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:33,440
That ten thousand of yours is all in stocks.

670
00:22:35,220 --> 00:22:36,160
Good heavens!

671
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,240
My money is all in stocks now?

672
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,519
Which stock did you end up buying?

673
00:22:41,519 --> 00:22:42,339
Let me check.

674
00:22:42,339 --> 00:22:44,599
The one that's a sure win?

675
00:22:44,759 --> 00:22:45,920
That's not necessarily true.

676
00:22:46,319 --> 00:22:47,480
Didn't I tell you?

677
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:49,640
Stocks that are a sure win...

678
00:22:49,799 --> 00:22:50,599
Enough.

679
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:53,359
Don't waste time lecturing me.

680
00:22:53,359 --> 00:22:55,359
I just want to know if I lost or made money.

681
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:56,279
Or what happened.

682
00:22:56,279 --> 00:22:57,920
Hurry up and call to check.

683
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,759
Here, let me help you.

684
00:22:58,819 --> 00:22:59,519
Let me help you.

685
00:22:59,519 --> 00:23:00,200
Okay.

686
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:00,619
What's the number?

687
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:01,319
What's the number? I'll help.

688
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,079
You are such a hassle.

689
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,039
Xiao Qian.

690
00:23:08,579 --> 00:23:09,839
Yes, it's Professor Fan.

691
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,839
That 10,000 yuan I gave you this morning.

692
00:23:12,559 --> 00:23:13,279
Right.

693
00:23:14,339 --> 00:23:15,019
What?

694
00:23:15,299 --> 00:23:16,099
Really?

695
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:19,519
Let's leave it at that for now.

696
00:23:19,519 --> 00:23:20,599
Okay, I'm hanging up.
